text: Jean-Denis Constant (born 1955), is a male former French international table tennis player. He won two bronze medals in the men's doubles at the 1973 World Table Tennis Championships and 1975 World Table Tennis Championships with Jacques Secrétin. ==See also== * List of table tennis players * List of World Table Tennis Championships medalists ==References== Category:French male table tennis players Category:1955 births Category:Living people Category:World Table Tennis Championships medalists
title: Jean-Denis Constant
